{
  "stem": "9262.3",
  "chunk_idx": 2,
  "model": "openai/gpt-oss-120b",
  "elapsed_s": 4.5,
  "sentences_input": [
    {
      "segment_idx": 6,
      "sentence_idx_in_seg": 10,
      "text": "People who know what the samovar is.",
      "word_count": 7
    },
    {
      "segment_idx": 6,
      "sentence_idx_in_seg": 11,
      "text": "It's like a urn, which keeps hot water, constant hot water.",
      "word_count": 11
    },
    {
      "segment_idx": 6,
      "sentence_idx_in_seg": 12,
      "text": "It's lit, I think, by a little coal fire, some kind of-- what they use for these-- what they call them-- where they have the picnics, you know, these little--",
      "word_count": 30
    },
    {
      "segment_idx": 7,
      "sentence_idx_in_seg": 0,
      "text": "No, not kerosene really because kerosene is liquid.",
      "word_count": 8
    },
    {
      "segment_idx": 7,
      "sentence_idx_in_seg": 1,
      "text": "These are like small little--",
      "word_count": 5
    },
    {
      "segment_idx": 8,
      "sentence_idx_in_seg": 0,
      "text": "[?",
      "word_count": 1
    },
    {
      "segment_idx": 8,
      "sentence_idx_in_seg": 1,
      "text": "I don't know. ?]",
      "word_count": 4
    },
    {
      "segment_idx": 9,
      "sentence_idx_in_seg": 0,
      "text": "[? --cubed ?] things.",
      "word_count": 4
    },
    {
      "segment_idx": 10,
      "sentence_idx_in_seg": 0,
      "text": "Yes.",
      "word_count": 1
    },
    {
      "segment_idx": 10,
      "sentence_idx_in_seg": 1,
      "text": "Sort of a stove, but a little bit different, where they heat the water.",
      "word_count": 14
    },
    {
      "segment_idx": 10,
      "sentence_idx_in_seg": 2,
      "text": "And it keeps it going throughout the Shabbat.",
      "word_count": 8
    },
    {
      "segment_idx": 10,
      "sentence_idx_in_seg": 3,
      "text": "It's always hot, especially in the winter.",
      "word_count": 7
    },
    {
      "segment_idx": 11,
      "sentence_idx_in_seg": 0,
      "text": "Oh, Shabbat was--",
      "word_count": 3
    },
    {
      "segment_idx": 12,
      "sentence_idx_in_seg": 0,
      "text": "Lots of songs, Shabbat songs, and the prayers.",
      "word_count": 8
    },
    {
      "segment_idx": 12,
      "sentence_idx_in_seg": 1,
      "text": "Just like being at a concert-- beautifully sung, beautifully chanted.",
      "word_count": 10
    },
    {
      "segment_idx": 12,
      "sentence_idx_in_seg": 2,
      "text": "And the ceremony of the Shabbat, when they cut the bread, the challah bread, the benediction.",
      "word_count": 16
    },
    {
      "segment_idx": 12,
      "sentence_idx_in_seg": 3,
      "text": "And then when they were sitting down and they had the first course, and in between the songs, the atmosphere was superb, really something nice, something which is kind of impregnated in your memory, especially when you see it in your childhood.",
      "word_count": 42
    },
    {
      "segment_idx": 12,
      "sentence_idx_in_seg": 4,
      "text": "A large family sitting around the Shabbat table, having nice songs and talking about these things that happen in the week and what's going on, what one would like to do in a peaceful atmosphere.",
      "word_count": 35
    },
    {
      "segment_idx": 12,
      "sentence_idx_in_seg": 5,
      "text": "Still no inkling about that war was on the doorstep.",
      "word_count": 10
    },
    {
      "segment_idx": 12,
      "sentence_idx_in_seg": 6,
      "text": "Going, for instance, to a butcher shop on a normal day in Poland, there was such a variety of meat you could choose.",
      "word_count": 23
    },
    {
      "segment_idx": 12,
      "sentence_idx_in_seg": 7,
      "text": "Chickens you could have, turkeys, geese, ducks.",
      "word_count": 7
    },
    {
      "segment_idx": 12,
      "sentence_idx_in_seg": 8,
      "text": "It was really a treasure, a kind of [INAUDIBLE] there.",
      "word_count": 10
    },
    {
      "segment_idx": 12,
      "sentence_idx_in_seg": 9,
      "text": "You could get anything, everything you wanted.",
      "word_count": 7
    },
    {
      "segment_idx": 12,
      "sentence_idx_in_seg": 10,
      "text": "As I said, there was a lot of poverty.",
      "word_count": 9
    },
    {
      "segment_idx": 12,
      "sentence_idx_in_seg": 11,
      "text": "But despite that, people had to eat.",
      "word_count": 7
    },
    {
      "segment_idx": 12,
      "sentence_idx_in_seg": 12,
      "text": "If they didn't have enough, they were given by neighbors.",
      "word_count": 10
    }
  ],
